\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.1}{\ignorespaces Model pipeline schematic for a single cross-validation fold. Raw features $\mathbf  {X}$ and target variable $\mathbf  {y}$ (\texttt  {age\_gap}) are split by client identity using GroupShuffleSplit. The training fold undergoes median imputation and scaling before model fitting; the same imputation parameters are applied to the test fold. Evaluation metrics are computed on the test fold predictions. This procedure is repeated 30 times with different random splits.}}{23}{figure.5.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pipeline}{{5.1}{23}{Model pipeline schematic for a single cross-validation fold. Raw features $\mathbf {X}$ and target variable $\mathbf {y}$ (\texttt {age\_gap}) are split by client identity using GroupShuffleSplit. The training fold undergoes median imputation and scaling before model fitting; the same imputation parameters are applied to the test fold. Evaluation metrics are computed on the test fold predictions. This procedure is repeated 30 times with different random splits}{figure.5.1}{}}
